# MRN Auto-completion and Auto-search Implementation Plan

This plan outlines the changes required to implement automatic MRN check digit completion and search triggering in the `AutoPrescribe` application's frontend.

## Proposed Changes

### [AutoPrescribe Frontend]

#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/Combined_Server/AutoPrescribe/templates/index.html)
- Add a listener to the `#chart-no` input field.
- Implement the check digit algorithm to calculate the 10th character (check digit) when exactly 9 digits are entered.
- Automatically update the input value with the calculated check digit.
- Trigger the [searchChart()](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/Combined_Server/AutoPrescribe/templates/index.html#387-395) function immediately after auto-completion.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. Open the AutoPrescribe application in a browser.
2. Navigate to the Patient Selection panel (after login).
3. Type 9 digits into the "Chart No Query" field (e.g., `003235483`).
4. Verify that:
   - The 10th character (e.g., `J`) is automatically appended.
   - The search is automatically triggered without clicking the "Search" button.
   - The status box displays "Querying chart [MRN]..." and results appear in the list.
